<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Brown" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Brown,</orth> adj. of a dusky colour: <cit><quote>b. bread,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.194" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 194</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. and white bastard,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 4</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.82" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 82</bibl>. <cit><quote>b. furze,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.1.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 1, 71</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>paper,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 5</bibl></cit>.* <cit><quote>thread,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 138</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>hair,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 48</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 4, 14</bibl> <cit><quote>(--er).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.4.9" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 4, 9</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>(--er).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 3, 35</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.11.14" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 11, 14</bibl>. <cit><quote>heads,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 20</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>she is too b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 174</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--er than her brother,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.89" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 89</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>as b. as hazelnuts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.256" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 256</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the b. wench,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.295" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 295</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a b. favour,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 101</bibl></cit>--105. -- <emph>a b. bill</emph> (cf. <emph>bill</emph>) <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.10.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 10, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 92</bibl> (a kind of halbert, whose name is of uncertain origin).<lb />Substantively: <cit><quote>though grey do something mingle with our younger b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 4.8.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 8, 20</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>